parameters:
Maid Kamari: The Crescent Necklace... Does the Academy have
any business with you, Master?

Mage Relm: I came here on a request from Crow. This great
genius will definitely solve it!
Clea: Is it possible for me to meet Mr. Crow?

Maid Kamari: Master, it seems you cannot sleep at night...
Please solve the mysterious phenomena occurring in the
mansion.
Maid Kamari: I will guide you to the master's room.
Clea: Is Kamari-san an important person?

Nobleman Crow: My research is not something to be praised,
but she is the only one who stays in the mansion without
making a displeased face.

Nobleman Crow: Moreover, when I drink her tea, it tastes
just like my deceased mother's comforting flavor...
Clea: He must be an important person.

Mage Relm: Not only the person herself, but there were no
issues with her clothes or the room itself.
Mage Relm: In that case, the mystery only deepens...

Nobleman Crow: I'm glad it wasn't Kamari as the cause. Now I
can request the guards to protect us with peace of mind.

Nobleman Crow: If you don't mind, how about having a meal?
Kamari's cooking is exquisite, so please enjoy it.

Thief Nora: Huh, is it really okay!? I haven't eaten
anything since lunch, so I'm getting hungry!

Nobleman Crow: Hahaha, it's already this late, so please
give me your thoughts on the magic I've been researching.

Nobleman Crow: All the strange phenomena occurred at night.
It's pointless to think about it now, but...

Nobleman Crow: Where is Kamari!? Could it be that she's
still in the basement...?!

Priestess Sophia: I was left behind in the room after
cleaning.

Clea: It might be convenient. I will now rescue Kamari-san
and solve the mystery phenomenon.

Nobleman Crow: I'm counting on you. If anything happens to
Kamari... I...
Nobleman Kuro Kamari... Please be safe.

Nobleman Crow: Is Kamari safe!? Please tell me in detail
what happened!

Mage Relm: I also have a question. Are you researching the
subordinate demon Dillark?
Nobleman Crow: Was it all my fault...

Mage Relm: I apologize for the disrespectful use of magic
that accidentally made Kamari a subordinate, but it was due
to Crow's imperfect magic.

Mage Relm: It is my prediction that it became a magic that
activates under specific conditions, and strange phenomena
should have occurred on the night when the guest arrived.

Nobleman Crow: That's right, I remember... I ordered for the
noisy guest to be silenced.

Nobleman Crow: But more importantly, is Kamari okay? Is she
safe!?

Mage Relm: Actually, it was the maid outfit she was wearing
that caused it. Kamari herself is fine, so don't worry!

Mage Relm: Hehe, if it's praise for this genius, it's very
much welcome!
Clea: Yes, you truly are an amazing mage.
Mage Relm: H-Heh, it feels strange to be praised normally...

Nobleman Crow: Kamari cherished wearing the same maid
outfit, and it was all because of my foolishness. How can I
make amends...

Maid Kamari: There is no need for compensation. I have
pledged my loyalty to the master who kindly took me in.

Maid Kamari: May I offer you this maid outfit? I thought it
could be put to good use in your [work], Master.
Nobleman Crow: Would you accept it as an additional reward?

Clea: Yes, we will take care of the management and
utilization.

Mage Relm: In terms of size... Clea-san seems like she could
wear it! It's not because my body is small or anything like
that!

Nobleman Crow: Thank you very much. Finally, it seems like
I'll be able to sleep peacefully.

Nobleman Kuro I can't thank you enough for this... Is it
strange for me to propose to a maid?

Maid Kamari: Lately, I've been feeling your gaze, Master.
Have I made some kind of mistake...?

Maid Kamari: I apologize for any inconvenience I may have
caused. If it's alright with you, please make use of this.
